<font color="#FF0000">THIS WEB SITE</font><br>
<tt>Sun Dec 15 11:08:06 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
This is the most exciting web site in the history of web sites.  I pray it will continue until I get time to reflect my thoughts on why Vietnam happened; I will do it soon.  I flew a combat in 1968 as an Air Force pilot, used to look down in the jungles of SEA every other day or so and say to myself, &quot;I wouldn't last a week down there&quot;.  This web site will become the national catharsis of the Vietnam debacle, and ease the pain of millions.  It will bring thkem back.  Moreover, it will provide enhanced visibility to national decision makers in conflict situations.  The conceptualizers, implementors and administrators of this site should be commended and continuously motivated to maintain these very high standards.  You folks will receive rewards/awards of a thousand fold.  My thanks.  Stewart R. Gable, Colonel USAF [Ret'd] [srg4444@primenet.com]
